Rate my Python code for finding prime numbers up to n:

def primes(n):
    sieve = [True] * n
    sieve[0] = sieve[1] = False
    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1):
        if sieve[i]:
            for j in range(i*i, n, i):
                sieve[j] = False
    return [i for i, is_prime in enumerate(sieve) if is_prime]

Is this efficient? Any improvements?
